commit.message:
Update metadata.json

Co-authored-by: Marco Trevisan <mail@3v1n0.net>

Update metadata.json

As of 46.alpha I have found that adding 46 into the shell version allows appindicator to work of Gnome 46 with out any other intervention.
util: Use TextDecoder to get strings from a bytes array
Update Hungarian translation
Update Russian translation
Release 57

statusNotifierWatcher: Fix disabling errors

Closes: #457
extension: Remove unneeded logging

Releasing v56

Version 55 has been eaten by e.g.o
settingsManager: Avoid using run_dispose() manually
Release 54
meson: Check files on source dir only
indicatorStatusIcon: Always try to use activation unless if marked as supported

indicatorStatusIcon: Do not use event fields directly

These are not exposed anymore, so activation of icons wouldn't work.
cleanup: Use Signals.EventEmitter instead of changing the prototypes
extension: Remove various version-dependent checks
eslint: Sync with current upstream gjs and shell rules

extension: Port to ESM module usage

Closes: https://github.com/ubuntu/gnome-shell-extension-appindicator/issues/454
dbusMenu: Use Clutter.ActorAlign instead of undefined St.Align
appIndicator: Do not warn on cancelled operation
Update Chinese translation
update PL translation
Update Turkish translation
Release 53

statusNotifierWatcher: Remove idle promise on bus seeking

We're already depending on promises that implies going waiting anyways, so
we can avoid this.
util: Use recursive generator to get introspection results

util: Use an async generator to iterate over bus objects

We need to do chunked requests to avoid initialization slowdowns, and
apparently awaiting many promises here is not as good as expected and may
lead to hanging, while using a generator is better, so  let's do this.

This implies bumping the required eslint version, while the the minimum
shell version should be ok, because gjs in GNOME 3.34 required mozjs60,
while async generators are supported since mozjs55.

Helps with: #295

dbusUtils: Use more reasonable timeout for introspection

No need to wait for hanging services forever, let's limit this to 5 seconds

dbusUtil: Filter introspectable bus by interfaces if provided

We can avoid doing it later by just not exposing the interfaces at all

statusNotifierWatcher: Properly handle null services

They may be added to the set in case they match service name
